{"word":"ἰωκή","slug":"ἰωκή","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἰωκή</b></el> <el>(ἰωκή, ἡ,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:διώκω'><el>διώκω</el></a>\n<p/><i>rout, pursuit</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>:— <el>Ἰωκή</el> is personified <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>metaplast. <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <el>ἴωκα</el> (as if from <el>ἰώξ</el>), <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>\n"}]}